yazpp
------------------------------------------
YAZ++ is an application programming interface (API) to YAZ which supports the
development of Z39.50/SRU/Solr client and server applications using C++. Like
YAZ, it supports Z39.50-2003 (version 3) as well as SRU version 1.1 thru 2.0 in
both the client and server roles. YAZ++ includes an implementation of the ZOOM
C++ binding and a generic client/server API based on the Observer/Observable
design pattern.

Runtime requirements:
  bash-4.4.12-3
  cygwin-3.1.7-1
  libgcc1-10.2.0-1
  libstdc++6-10.2.0-1
  libyaz5-5.23.1-2
  libyazpp6-1.7.1-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-10.2.0-1
  gcc-g++-10.2.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-7
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://www.indexdata.com/resources/software/yazpp/

Canonical download:
  http://ftp.indexdata.dk/pub/yazpp/yazpp-1.7.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack yazpp-1.7.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./yazpp-1.7.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/yazpp-1.7.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/yazpp-1.7.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libyazpp6-1.7.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libyazpp-devel-1.7.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

